about.description:
Confuse is a configuration library for Python that uses YAML.
It takes care of defaults, overrides, type checking, command-line
integration, human-readable errors, and standard OS-specific locations.

name: confuse
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "confuse" %}
{% set version = "1.1.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: adc1979ea6f4c0dd3d6fe06020c189843a649082ab8f6fb54db16f4ac5e5e1da

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - pyyaml

test:
  imports:
    - confuse

about:
  home: https://github.com/beetbox/confuse
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: painless YAML configuration

  description: |
    Confuse is a configuration library for Python that uses YAML.
    It takes care of defaults, overrides, type checking, command-line
    integration, human-readable errors, and standard OS-specific locations.
  doc_url: http://confuse.readthedocs.org/
  dev_url: https://github.com/beetbox/confuse

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - philip-khor
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.15
